         <component>
            <section ID="ID_AF7DA939-79A3-309A-4E66-447267DCBC76">
               <id root="7d648abf-5d3b-16e8-e053-2991aa0aa50d"/>
               <code code="34088-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="OVERDOSAGE SECTION"/>
               <title>OVERDOSAGE</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Topically applied Clindamycin Phosphate Topical Solution can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects (see 
       
 
  <content styleCode="bold">
                        <linkHtml href="#ID_600e9952-4d00-a7fd-c176-7a2043156d0a">WARNINGS</linkHtml>
                     </content>). 
      

 </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20150402"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="ID_AC38E7A3-94B5-6A48-778F-CC14993C430D">
               <id root="7d648abf-5d3c-16e8-e053-2991aa0aa50d"/>
               <code code="34068-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <title>DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Apply a thin film of Clindamycin Phosphate Topical Solution twice daily to affected area. Keep all liquid dosage forms in containers tightly closed. </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20160914"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
